comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-11T16:13:53.661Z",validate-autofix-agent,"Implemented details.missing_by_type on the metadata check: { <ItemType>: { <field>: count } }, zero-suppressed at both levels, sorted lexicographically, and restricted to the ACTIVE metadata profile's required fields so it mirrors details.counts at type granularity. Counts only (never row dumps) for token efficiency; per-field item-id lists remain the existing verbose-diagnostics surface. Pure aggregation lives in src/core/validate/missing-by-type.ts (fully unit-tested)."
close_reason: Added per-item-type missing-required-field grouping to pm validate --check-metadata
